The following code crashes the compiler in 2.8.RC1:
{code}
class Test { 
  val a = new Container.GenericClass()
}

object Container extends Container

class Container {
  class GenericClass[T](arg: String = "")
}
{code}

If we delete the constructor invocation or if we move the !GenericClass at the top level or in an object the code compiles without problems.

The stacktrace produced when trying to compile the above code:
